11. nee.. ‚et, ‘not only not...but also.’

Cinyphius. The Cinyps was a small river in Africa (Syr- tica). The goats which fed near it were famed for the beauty and softness of their hair. Verg. Georg. 111. 312.

Martial means that the fieece of the goat on the patera was of such exceptional beauty that a Cinyphian herdsman, aecus- tomed to shear the beautiful hair of his own goats, would not like to meddle with it.
